tempAlarm13.name: tempAlarm13
tempAlarm13.description: A tempAlarm indicates a temperature sensor has changed its state from underThreshold(4) to overThreshold(3).

moduleChange13.name: moduleChange13
moduleChange13.description: A moduleChange trap occurs when a module is inserted or removed from the chassis.

powerEvent13.name: powerEvent13
powerEvent13.description: A powerEvent trap occurs when a power supply is inserted or removed from the chassis, or a problem condition is recognized on a power supply.

controllerEvent13.name: controllerEvent13
controllerEvent13.description: A controlEvent trap occurs when a chassis controller (MPM) loses or gains the state of master(3). If this is due to chassis controller being inserted or removed from the slot, a moduleChange trap will also be sent.

loginViolation13.name: loginViolation13
loginViolation13.description: A loginViolation trap occurs when a login attempt fails due to an incorrect login-id or password.

macVlanViolation13.name: macVlanViolation13
macVlanViolation13.description: A macVlanViolation trap occurs when a frame is received from a port with a VLAN ID different from the VLAN where the frame previously has received.

macDuplicatePort13.name: macDuplicatePort13
macDuplicatePort13.description: A macDuplicatePort trap occurs when a frame is received from a source port different from the port where the frame previously has received although they both ports belong to the same VLAN.

portLinkUpEvent13.name: portLinkUpEvent13
portLinkUpEvent13.description: A portLinkTrap occurs whenever a phy, log, or virt port is enabled.

portLinkDownEvent13.name: portLinkDownEvent13
portLinkDownEvent13.description: A portLinkTrap occurs whenever a phy, log, or virt port is disabled.

portPartitioned13.name: portPartitioned13
portPartitioned13.description: A portPartioned trap occurs when the physical port has transitioned thru enable/disable states faster than 10 times in the past second...indicative of a flakey cable.

portRecordMismatch13.name: portRecordMismatch13
portRecordMismatch13.description: A portRecordMismatch trap occurs when the specified port data is found to be diferent than the privious configuration. Typically this will be generated when a NIC of one type is swapped out for a DIFFERENT type. IE ethernet for fddi, atm for token-ring, etc...

groupChange13.name: groupChange13
groupChange13.description: A groupChange trap occurs whenever a group is created or deleted from the system via the UI or SNMP. The group and status code are sent as part of the variable binding. The status codes are: 1 - disable 2 - enable 3 - delete 4 - create 5 - modify (see xylan-vport MIB)

vlanChange13.name: vlanChange13
vlanChange13.description: A vlanChange trap occurs whenever a VLAN is created or deleted from the system via the UI or SNMP. The group, vlan and status code are sent as part of the variable binding. See groupChange for the status codes.

portMove13.name: portMove13
portMove13.description: A portMove trap occurs when the specified port is moved from a group/vlan or has had its configuration changed.

moduleResetReload13.name: moduleResetReload13
moduleResetReload13.description: A moduleResetReload trap occurs when the specified module has been reset or reloaded by the chassis mgr.

systemEvent13.name: systemEvent13
systemEvent13.description: A systemEvent trap occurs when a potentially fatal system error occurrs. Such as: out of FLASH/ memory space. The event type is in the var bind. A Descriptive string MAY be present. The following trap numbers are defined (see xylan-trapc.mib): 10 Unspecified log event 11 Log file full 12 Log file erased 20 Unspecified memory event 21 Memory shortage 30 Unsepcified CPU event 31 Long term CPU overload 32 Short term CPU overload 40 Unspecified ffs event 41 Attempt to write to full ffs 42 System/user directed purge 43 Removed imgs/cfgs 44 Exec file removed 45 Config file removed 46 Exec file updated 47 Config file updated 50 Unspecified chassis event 51 Module failed to init 52 Module failed to load 53 Module startup failed 54 Module failed 55 Driver failed

vlanRouteTableFull13.name: vlanRouteTableFull13
vlanRouteTableFull13.description: A vlanRouteTableFull trap occurs when either the IP or IPX route table is full. (discovered on insertion attempt)

sapTableFull13.name: sapTableFull13
sapTableFull13.description: A sapTableFull trap occurs when the IPX SAP table is found to be full on insertion.

atmSSCOPstate13.name: atmSSCOPstate13
atmSSCOPstate13.description: A atmSSCOPstate trap occurs when the signalling state for the specified physical port changes.

ilmiState13.name: ilmiState13
ilmiState13.description: A ilmiState trap occurs when the ILMI state for the specified physical port changes.

atmConnection13.name: atmConnection13
atmConnection13.description: A atmConnection trap occurs when the specified ATM Vcc is created or deleted.

atmService13.name: atmService13
atmService13.description: A atmService trap occurs when the specified ATM service is created or deleted>

dlciUp13.name: dlciUp13
dlciUp13.description: Frame-Relay Dlci Just Changed to Active

dlciDn13.name: dlciDn13
dlciDn13.description: Frame-Relay Dlci Just Changed to InActive

portManualForwardingMode13.name: portManualForwardingMode13
portManualForwardingMode13.description: A portManualForwardingMode trap occurs when the specified port is placed into manual mode forwarding as its default setting whenever the port is assigned to a Group that is participating in the IBM spanning tree algorithm.

fddiCFStateChange13.name: fddiCFStateChange13
fddiCFStateChange13.description: A fddiCFStateChange trap occurs when the specified fddi physical port changes from wrap configuration state.

duplicateIPaddress13.name: duplicateIPaddress13
duplicateIPaddress13.description: A duplicateIPaddress trap occurs whenever the switch detects a duplicate IP address.

duplicateMACaddress13.name: duplicateMACaddress13
duplicateMACaddress13.description: A duplicateMACaddress trap occurs whenever the switch detects a duplicate MAC address of one of its own router ports.

healthThresholdRising13.name: healthThresholdRising13
healthThresholdRising13.description: A healthThresholdRising trap occurs when at least one of the user-specified thresholds is exceeded for the first time.

healthThresholdFalling13.name: healthThresholdFalling13
healthThresholdFalling13.description: A healthThresholdFalling trap occurs when at least one of the user-specified thresholds was exceeded during the previous cycle and none of them are exceeded this cycle.

healthThresholdDevice13.name: healthThresholdDevice13
healthThresholdDevice13.description: A healthThresholdDevice trap occurs when at least one device-level threshold crossing is detected.

healthThresholdModule13.name: healthThresholdModule13
healthThresholdModule13.description: A healthThresholdModule trap occurs when at least one module-level threshold crossing is detected.

healthThresholdPort13.name: healthThresholdPort13
healthThresholdPort13.description: A healthThresholdPort trap occurs when at least one port-level threshold crossing is detected.

xylanXIPXMAPPortStatusChange13.name: xylanXIPXMAPPortStatusChange13
xylanXIPXMAPPortStatusChange13.description: A xylanXIPXMAPPortStatusChange trap occurs when a change in status occurs in an XMAP-tracked virtual port.

xylanXIPXMAPStateChange13.name: xylanXIPXMAPStateChange13
xylanXIPXMAPStateChange13.description: A xylanXIPXMAPStateChange trap occurs when XMAP is turned on or off.

avlAuthAttempt13.name: avlAuthAttempt13
avlAuthAttempt13.description: The last Authenticated VLAN authentication attempt.

xylanXIPGMAPFailedUpdate13.name: xylanXIPGMAPFailedUpdate13
xylanXIPGMAPFailedUpdate13.description: A xylanXIPGMAPFailedUpdate trap occurs when GMAP is unable to update the forwarding database to reflect information in its internal database.

clkBusLineStateChange13.name: clkBusLineStateChange13
clkBusLineStateChange13.description: A clkBusLineStateChange trap occurs when 1 of the following occurs at the 8k or the 19m bus line: 1) bus line's status changes (active or inactive) 2) clock switching has occured The following are sent as part of the variable binding: Status code: inactive - 1 active - 2 Bus line: eightKhz - 1 nineteenMhz - 2

bind_violation13.name: bind_violation13
bind_violation13.description: A bind-violation trap occurs whenever a binding rule which has been configured gets violated.

phyPortPartition13.name: phyPortPartition13
phyPortPartition13.description: A phyPortPartition trap occurs when the device detects link state is active for a physical port, but line errors, or system behaviour, indicate that the cable/media is unuseable. The device will then force the disabling of the port in question and generate this trap. The device will retry using the port in question should a cable drop occur, which may indicate a user has attempted to fix the bad media.

policyEvent13.name: policyEvent13
policyEvent13.description: This trap signifies that the switch subagent has detected that the event represented by eventIndex has occurred in the switch.

pnniRouteConflictPort13.name: pnniRouteConflictPort13
pnniRouteConflictPort13.description: This trap occurs when PNNI detects that a static route on the pnnixIfPortId port has been created and this port has been configured as a PNNI port. This may cause mis-routing in a PNNI network if the port turns out to be an Inside port.

pnniRouteConflictSamePG13.name: pnniRouteConflictSamePG13
pnniRouteConflictSamePG13.description: This trap occurs when PNNI detects that a static route on the pnnixIfPortId port has been created and this route matches (a prefix of) the Peer Group ID. This may cause mis-routing in a PNNI network.

xPnniFilterAlarm13.name: xPnniFilterAlarm13
xPnniFilterAlarm13.description: An alarm indicating that a PNNI filter has denied access to a call attempt. The filter denying the access is identified in the variable.

xPnniPmPThresholdReached13.name: xPnniPmPThresholdReached13
xPnniPmPThresholdReached13.description: An alarm indicating that no more Point-to-Multipoint calls may be established until ongoing PMP calls are released due to capacity restrictions of the local fabric.

xPnniDtlTableExhaustion13.name: xPnniDtlTableExhaustion13
xPnniDtlTableExhaustion13.description: An alarm indicating that no more calls may be established due to capacity restrictions of the DTL Table.

xPnniNeighborFailure13.name: xPnniNeighborFailure13
xPnniNeighborFailure13.description: An alarm indicating that a neighbor on a particular port has ceased communication with this switching system.

xPnniNodeDown13.name: xPnniNodeDown13
xPnniNodeDown13.description: An alarm indicating that a PNNI node (instance) within this switching system has been disabled and the reason. If the reason is due to remote action, the IP address causing the action is specified in the trap.

xPnniLinkFailure13.name: xPnniLinkFailure13
xPnniLinkFailure13.description: An alarm indicating that a particular port has transitioned from operational state within this switching system.

fddiLerFlagChange13.name: fddiLerFlagChange13
fddiLerFlagChange13.description: A fddiLerFlagChange trap occurs when the LER flag on a port changes from CLEAR to SET.

fddiLCTFailCntIncr13.name: fddiLCTFailCntIncr13
fddiLCTFailCntIncr13.description: A fddiLCTFailCntIncr trap occurs when the LCT flag on a port is incremented.

mpcStatisticsOverflow13.name: mpcStatisticsOverflow13
mpcStatisticsOverflow13.description: A statistic overflow trap occurs when a paticular entry of mpcStatisticsTable reach the threshold value, the paticular statistics is identified by statisticsNum of trap data which is the entry index of the mpcStatisticsTable. The current threshold valye is hard coded to 2024. The Trap PDU data format: struct { unsigned int mpcIndex; Index of MPC unsigned int statisticsNum; Entry Index of mpcStatisticsTable unsigned long statisticsThreshold; Trap Threshold Value of Entry unsigned long statisticsValue; Current Statistics Value of Entry } where statisticsNum, statisticsThreshold and statisticsValue entry attached with objecid mpcStatRxMpoaResolveReplyInsufECResources

mpcShortCut13.name: mpcShortCut13
mpcShortCut13.description: A shortcut trap occurs when the shortcut path established, closed or failed to complete path. event type: 01 shortcut established 02 shortcut closed 03 failed to complete path The Trap PDU data format: struct { unsigned int event_type; unsigned int vcNumber; VCI number of destination unsigned int prototype; 1: IP, 11: IPX unsigned char destNet_addr[10]; IP or IPX address of destination unsigned char destAtm_addr[20]; ATM address of destination unsigned int mpcIndex; Index of MPC unsigned int mpsIndex; Index of MPS }

mpcIngressRetryTimeOut13.name: mpcIngressRetryTimeOut13
mpcIngressRetryTimeOut13.description: A ingress retry timeout trap occurs when the retry time exceed the MPC-p5 time. The Trap PDU data format: struct { unsigned int mpcIndex; Index of MPC unsigned int max_timeout_sec; Timeout value in second unsigned char destNet_addr[10]; IP or IPX address of destination unsigned char destAtm_addr[20]; ATM address of destination unsigned int prototype; 1: IP, 11: IPX unsigned int mpsIndex; Index of MPS }

oamVCAIS13.name: oamVCAIS13
oamVCAIS13.description: This trap signifies that the specified connection is in VC-AIS state.

oamVCRDI13.name: oamVCRDI13
oamVCRDI13.description: This trap signifies that the specified connection is in VC-RDI state.

oamVCLOC13.name: oamVCLOC13
oamVCLOC13.description: This trap signifies that the specified connection is in VC-LOC state.

oamVCUnsuccessLoop13.name: oamVCUnsuccessLoop13
oamVCUnsuccessLoop13.description: This trap signifies that the specified connection is unsuccessful Loopback state.

oamVPAIS13.name: oamVPAIS13
oamVPAIS13.description: This trap signifies that the specified VP connection is in VP-AIS state.

oamVPRDI13.name: oamVPRDI13
oamVPRDI13.description: This trap signifies that the specified VP connection is in VP-RDI state.

oamVPLOC13.name: oamVPLOC13
oamVPLOC13.description: This trap signifies that the specified VP connection is in VP-LOC state.

oamVPUnsuccessLoop13.name: oamVPUnsuccessLoop13
oamVPUnsuccessLoop13.description: This trap signifies that the specified VP connection is in Unsuccessful loopback state.

ldpPeerCreate13.name: ldpPeerCreate13
ldpPeerCreate13.description: A LDP peer is identified by LDP Hello mechanism and peer entry is created.

ldpPeerDelete13.name: ldpPeerDelete13
ldpPeerDelete13.description: A LDP peer is lost and peer entry is deleted.

ldpSessionCreate13.name: ldpSessionCreate13
ldpSessionCreate13.description: A LDP session with the peer is established and a session entry is created.

ldpSessionDelete13.name: ldpSessionDelete13
ldpSessionDelete13.description: A LDP session with the peer is lost and session entry is deleted.

accountEvent13.name: accountEvent13
accountEvent13.description: An account event is generated to signal that a new accounting file is available on the switch.

accountOver1Event13.name: accountOver1Event13
accountOver1Event13.description: This event is generated when the filling level exceeds the first threshold. This event is for information only, and signals that accounting data are accumulating on the switch.

accountUnder1Event13.name: accountUnder1Event13
accountUnder1Event13.description: This event is generated when the filling level goes below the first threshold. This event is for information only.

accountOver2Alarm13.name: accountOver2Alarm13
accountOver2Alarm13.description: This alarm is generated when the filling level exceeds the second threshold. It signals that the switch changes over to the alternate collection device.

accountUnder2Event13.name: accountUnder2Event13
accountUnder2Event13.description: This event is generated when the filling level is lowering below the second threshold.

accountOver3Alarm13.name: accountOver3Alarm13
accountOver3Alarm13.description: This event is generated when the filling level exceeds the third threshold. It signals that the switch is now in congestion.

accountUnder3Event13.name: accountUnder3Event13
accountUnder3Event13.description: This event is generated when the filling level is lowering below the third threshold.

accountNoDeviceAlarm13.name: accountNoDeviceAlarm13
accountNoDeviceAlarm13.description: This alarm is generated when the TCP connection establishment fails with both the primary and the secondary collection devices.

accountFileAlarm13.name: accountFileAlarm13
accountFileAlarm13.description: This alarm is generated when too many files are awaiting collection.

lecStateChangeEvent13.name: lecStateChangeEvent13
lecStateChangeEvent13.description: When a Lec status changes, a trap message will be send out to a network manager, the trap packet has the data format: struct { unsigned int lec_id; unsigned char elan_name[33]; unsigned char atm_addr[20]; unsigned int slot_number; unsigned int port_number; unsigned int service_number; unsigned int new_state; unsigned int pre_state; unsigned int reason_of_change; }

fantrayEvent13.name: fantrayEvent13
fantrayEvent13.description: A fantrayEvent trap occurs when a problem condition is recognized on a chassis fan tray.

sonetAisTypeTrap13.name: sonetAisTypeTrap13
sonetAisTypeTrap13.description: This trap is generated when there is any of the following AIS types of errors on Sonet PMC SONET_LINK_RX_AIS, SEC_LINE_AIS, SEC_PATH_AIS.

sonetRdiTypeTrap13.name: sonetRdiTypeTrap13
sonetRdiTypeTrap13.description: This trap is generated when there is any of the following RDI types of errors on Sonet SONET_LINK_RX_RDI, SEC_LINE_RDI, SEC_PATH_RDI.
